&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you a qualified Specialist Community Public Health Nurse (school nursing)?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Or a Specialist Community Public Health Nurse (health visiting)?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Do you have a passion in supporting children and young people aged 5-19 years and would like to complete the school nurse module in order to achieve this and subsequently work in school nursing?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Would you like a new challenge in a new area?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If so, read on……&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are really excited to offer this opportunity in line with Derbyshire County Council who are making a commitment to invest in school nursing for Derbyshire children and Young people, in order to improve health outcomes for this age group.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to appoint an innovative and motivated SCPHN to join our 5-19 workforce within the wider 0-19 Children’s service team in Derbyshire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post will be based within South Derbyshire and Derbyshire Dales locality, and will be working across this locality but based in Swadlincote.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The 5-19 service has a strong emphasis on meeting the public health needs of the local population and in recent months, different ways of engaging and supporting families and young people have been undertaken, taking into account social distancing and the use of technology, including the implementation of Chat Health.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tricia Bradshaw, Locality Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;tricia.bradshaw@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;07767 647649&lt;/p&gt;
